@@WThe Midgaard Gate Road@@N~
The @@Wash-mortar paving@@N of Roc Road begins here at the threshold of @@BMidgaard's West Gate@@N, stretching westward in a broad two-wagon lane between rows of stone @@Wcharter marker slabs@@N.  The road surface is the characteristic gray-purple aggregate of the city's oldest civic works, worn smooth by centuries of wheel ruts and boot-heels.  @@BRoad warden sigils@@N are freshly repainted on every upright surface, each one a small declaration that jurisdiction extends beyond the walls.  A tall @@ypetition board@@N stands beside the first relay station, its surface layered with weather-worn complaint notices and official response stamps dating back generations.  Drainage channels cut with precision along both verges carry rainwater away from the road-bed in the careful geometry of the @@WLantern Reforms@@N, functional after all these centuries.

